data.text:
The Milo Andrus Family Organization is a dedicated group based in Brigham City, UT, focused on preserving and celebrating the legacy of Milo Andrus, a prominent figure in Mormon history. With a comprehensive website offering genealogy research reports, newsletters, and resources, the organization aims to connect and engage members through reunions and volunteer opportunities.

Marking their calendars for the next family reunion in June 2022, the Milo Andrus Family Organization invites extended family members to join them at Chapel Park in Bountiful, Utah, for a day filled with activities and connections. With a commitment to ongoing research, the organization also shares the latest DNA findings and news updates to deepen their understanding of their heritage.
